   <mods:abstract>Pages 1-7 of this file contain the letter signed version of Jay's letter
            to Floridablanca of this date, covering Jay's Autograph Document Signed "General
            Propositions" for a Spanish-American Treaty. The remaining manuscripts in the file are
            Spanish translations of Jay's communications of this date and comments and summaries of
            the documents by Spanish officials. Jay submits treaty propositions: 1. peace and
            friendship with each other forever; 2. most favored nation privileges in commerce; 3.
            protection of each other's vessels; 4. no entrance into ports from which the vessels of
            most favored nation is excluded; 5. will accept Spanish contraband list; 6. the United
            States will forbear to use the Mississippi from 31 degrees to mouth (Jay's comment:
            hopes the disadvantages of this art. will be alleviated by the grant of a free port or
            some other compensation). 7. Spain and the United States will guarantee each other's
            territories.</mods:abstract>
